emotes.msg: Who's there? I..I've got an icicle!
I'm not dangerous. See? I'm smiling.
Have you seen my eyes around?
Much more of this and I'm going to become an Unhappy Snowman.
HasSnowGlobeNeydisa
HasSnowGlobeCabin
HasSnowGlobeSnowman
GivenBlindSnowmanPeppermint
KillTaskThreeEyedSnowmanwait
Talk
Hooray! My Perfect Eye!
Oh wait, you already gave me back my eye. This must be some other poor Snowman's eye. You keep it safe until you find out whose it is.
You must wait %tqt before turning this item in again.
Ah, more coal? You are very kind, but I have all I need to refashion my eyes. It may take some time, but you have helped me enough. Here, have this back in case you lose your eyes.
Ah, more coal? You are very kind, but I have all I need to refashion my eyes. It may take some time, but you have helped me enough. Here, have this back in case you lose your eyes.
What's this?
A stick? Well, my left arm has been acting up a bit, only in the warm weather though.
The Blind Snowman raises the peppermint stick to his carrot and sniffs.
Oh, another peppermint stick! Well, you've been so generous that I don't need any more. Have it back.
Perhaps you could get something from the drudges for it. I hear they love sweets.
Talk
Excellent, I hope that teaches ol' Three Eye a lesson. Here a little secret I found in the snow the other day.
KillTaskThreeEyedSnowmanwait
KillTaskThreeEyedSnowman
HeardBlindSnowmanSadStory
Hooray! My Perfect Eye! I'll have to clean it and polish it and maybe refacet it again, but at least I have it back.
Thank you, thank you. Here you deserve a reward for all of your help. Let's see... well not see per se... one second.
The Blind Snowman scoops up a pile of snow and casts a spell. The snow coalesces forming ice crystals that shift and rearrange as if alive.
HasSnowGlobeNeydisa
I can't be sure it turned out exactly right, but I hope you like it.
May your bottom stay cold and your eyes stay put. Soon I'll be able to see the snow again!
The Blind Snowman attempts to swallow the Perfect Snowman Eye, but after a lot of coughing just sticks it in his pocket.
What's this, a lump of coal? It's huge!
Wohoo! Thank you! I'll be able to make a huge set of eyes with this once it gets cold enough! I'll bet I'll be able to see better than any other snowman with my new huge eyes.
You deserve a reward for your good deed. Let's see... well not see per se... one second.
The Blind Snowman scoops up a pile of snow and casts a spell. The snow coalesces forming ice crystals that shift and rearrange as if alive.
HasSnowGlobeCabin
I can't be sure it turned out exactly right, but I hope you like it.
May your bottom stay cold and your eyes stay put. Soon I'll be able to see the snow again!
The Blind Snowman attempts to swallow the Huge Lump of Coal, but after a lot of coughing just sticks it in his pocket.
I can't believe it! It happened again!
There I was putting the finishing touches on my masterpiece. An eye so perfect, I would be able to see the individual beauty of a snowflake a mile away.
I heard a crunching and sliding in the snow nearby. I'm pretty sure it was a Snowman since it said...
The Blind Snowman makes a face and says in a cold nasty voice, "Whatcha got there melt bottom? That looks like a pretty nice eye! You won't mind if I take that will ya? Yoink!"

Then he grabbed my Perfect Eye! You have to get it back for me. I heard him exclaim as he bounced out of hearing that he was going to use it as a third eye so he could see better to hit people with iceballs. The villain!
Go and find the Three Eyed Snowman and get me back my eye. And teach that no good Three Eye a lesson. Kill him five times and maybe he will learn not to go around stealing other peoples dreams.
HeardBlindSnowmanSadStory

I will not fight for I follow the Path of the Snowflake.
I had a Seeing Eye Drudge, but he thought yellow snow was funny.
I would go for a walk, but some nasty little beast stole my Peppermint Stick!
I'm really worried that a fire elemental might come by. Normally I could run and hide. Maybe I'll try building a snow castle.
One person suggested I use diamonds for eyes. I tried that and it was really pretty, but the thousand little views made me toss snow.
